Sentencas: Part I of this study presented a computational model-based approach for enhancing the performance of solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) with designed microarchitecture.
Titulo: Microarchitectured solid oxide fuel cells with improved energy efficiency (Part II): Fabrication and characterization

Sentencas: The performance of such SOFCs was predicted to greatly improve through a systematic computational design and optimization approach.
Titulo: Microarchitectured solid oxide fuel cells with improved energy efficiency (Part II): Fabrication and characterization

Sentencas: Part II here proves through experimental fabrication and characterization that microarchitectured SOFC performance can be improved as predicted by the model.
Titulo: Microarchitectured solid oxide fuel cells with improved energy efficiency (Part II): Fabrication and characterization

Sentencas: A real and specific SOFC is chosen, fabricated and characterized to demonstrate the proof-of-concept.
Titulo: Microarchitectured solid oxide fuel cells with improved energy efficiency (Part II): Fabrication and characterization

Sentencas: Fabrication techniques using sintering and laser ablation are demonstrated.
Titulo: Microarchitectured solid oxide fuel cells with improved energy efficiency (Part II): Fabrication and characterization

Sentencas: Pore size and geometry are characterized by interferometry-based surface profilometry and scanning electron microscopy.
Titulo: Microarchitectured solid oxide fuel cells with improved energy efficiency (Part II): Fabrication and characterization

Sentencas: SOFC button cell performance testing including power output performance and electrochemical impedance spectroscopy are performed.
Titulo: Microarchitectured solid oxide fuel cells with improved energy efficiency (Part II): Fabrication and characterization

Sentencas: The results show that SOFC performance in a microarchitectured cell can be improved over a baseline button cell by 9-17% in current density and by 7-19% in power density.
Titulo: Microarchitectured solid oxide fuel cells with improved energy efficiency (Part II): Fabrication and characterization
